{"questionId":"9077013","questionHtml":"<p>In a fresh pure sample of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{}_{15}^{32}{\\text{P}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>15</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>32</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;the activity of the sample is 24 Bq. After one week&nbsp;the activity has become 17 Bq. Calculate, in s<sup>–1</sup>, the decay constant of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{}_{15}^{32}{\\text{P}}\">\n  <msubsup>\n    <mrow>\n\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>15</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>32</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </msubsup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>1 week = 6.05&nbsp;× 10<sup>5</sup>&nbsp;«s»</p>\n<p>17 = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"24{{\\text{e}}^{ - \\lambda&nbsp; \\times 6.1 \\times {{10}^5}}}\">\n  <mn>24</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>e</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mi>λ</mi>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mn>6.1</mn>\n        <mo>×</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mn>5</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p>5.7&nbsp;× 10<sup>−7&nbsp;</sup>«s<sup>–1</sup>» ✔<br><br></p>\n<p><em>Award<strong> [2 max]</strong> if answer is not in seconds</em></p>\n<p><em>If answer <strong>not</strong> in seconds and <strong>no</strong> unit quoted award<strong> [1 max]</strong> for correct substitution into equation (MP2)</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9077013","referenceCode":"18N.2.HL.TZ0.d.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"In a fresh pure sample of 15 32 P the a